description:
Boys & Girls I Love The 90's The Compilation (2014)


Although their history dates back much further, the '90s could be considered a golden age for boy bands, girl groups, and other polished mainstream vocal pop acts. The Backstreet Boys, Salt-N-Pepa, *NSYNC, Wilson Phillips, and the Spice Girls all ubiquitously ruled the airwaves for a time, while similarly minded solo acts like Britney Spears and Christina Aguilera launched their careers in the latter part of the decade. There were mixed-gender vocal groups like Ace of Base and mixed-race groups like Color Me Badd. This is the music that is celebrated on the collection I Love the 90's: Boys & Girls Edition. Wet Wet Wet, En Vogue, Boyzone, TLC, Hanson, and many more are all ready to sex you up and pillow talk you to death over the course of two discs and 42 songs.
